After months of development and beta testing, Sellfaster is officially live. This release brings a complete platform rebuild — everything your door-to-door sales team needs to canvass smarter, close faster, and get paid accurately. Here is everything that is new.

## Terminology Updates

We have refined the language of the platform to better reflect how sales teams actually work.

- **Projects → Campaigns.** The units of work your team is organized around are now called campaigns. This better reflects that each canvassing effort has a defined scope, territory, and timeline.
- **Addresses → Leads.** Every location your team tracks is now called a lead, aligning the platform with standard sales terminology and making it easier to onboard new reps.

---

## Map & Territory

### Revamped Map View

The map has been completely rebuilt. Leads are displayed as color-coded markers that cluster at higher zoom levels, zones are rendered as colored polygon overlays, and you can overlay interaction and sale markers to see exactly what is happening in each territory. Toggle layers on and off, filter by zone, interaction state, product, sale state, or date range — all without leaving the map.

[SCREENSHOT: Campaign map with zone overlays, clustered lead markers, and interaction markers visible]

### Lead Generation Based on Zones

Draw a zone polygon directly on the map and Sellfaster will automatically extract all addresses and businesses from OpenStreetMap data within that boundary as ready-to-work leads. No CSV import, no manual entry — just draw and go. Zones can be colour-coded, assigned to specific reps, and used as the scope for bonus targets, giving you a complete territory management workflow out of the box.

---

## Leads & Data

### Custom Fields for Leads

Teams can define their own fields on lead records — text, numbers, dates, or dropdowns. Custom fields appear in the lead form, the leads table as optional columns, and are fully searchable and filterable. They work in structured queries (`cf:field_key = "value"`) and in saved views.

### Team-Wide Interaction States

Interaction states — the stages a lead moves through in your sales process (e.g., No Answer, Interested, Appointment Requested) — are now managed at the team level and assigned to campaigns. States can be configured with colors, follow-up requirements, and campaign assignments, giving every manager a consistent view across all territories.

[SCREENSHOT: Interaction states configuration screen with color-coded state badges]

### AI-Assisted Search

The lead search now supports three modes: simple text search, a structured JQL-like query language, and a new AI mode. In AI mode, you type a plain-language query ("show me leads in Berlin that are interested") and the system translates it into precise filters automatically. Structured queries support custom fields, multiple operators, and AND/OR logic.

### Saved Views

Configure your lead list with filters, search mode, column visibility, sort order, and page size — then save the entire configuration as a named view. Load any saved view in one click from your personal account menu. Views can be reordered, renamed, and given custom icons.

---

## Email

Send and receive emails with leads directly inside Sellfaster — no switching between tools. Add a custom field of type `email` to your lead template, connect your own SMTP server (and optionally an IMAP server for reply tracking), and a compose button appears on every lead that has an email address on file. Sent emails are automatically logged as interactions on the lead, replies are captured and threaded when IMAP is configured, and the full conversation history sits alongside visits, calls, and notes in one place. Your team's sender name, from address, and signature are configured once in team settings and apply to every outgoing message.

