## Sales & Inventory

### Inventory System

Products are now managed in a central inventory. Each product has a name, description, price, per-unit commission amount, and optional quantity tracking. Products can be assigned to specific campaigns to control availability, and stock movements (shipments in and out) are logged for full traceability. On top of that, you can run **promotions** on any product — set a date range and a promotional price or commission override, and the system applies it automatically during that period. Promotions are tracked on every affected sale and commission entry so the numbers always add up correctly.

[SCREENSHOT: Inventory page showing product list with quantity and commission columns]

### Configurable Sale Models

Sale models define the entire lifecycle of a sale: which states it can be in (e.g., Proposal, Confirmed, Cancelled), which transitions are allowed, when commission is earned, and when it is reclaimed. Teams can create multiple models, assign them per campaign, and configure auto-transitions that advance a sale after a set number of days — for example, auto-confirming a proposal after a 14-day cooling-off period.

### Orders

Orders group multiple sales to the same customer into a single record, making it easier to track multi-product deals and generate accurate commission summaries for complex transactions.

