## Commission & Payouts

### Custom Commission Report Templates

Upload a `.docx` template with placeholders and every generated payslip will match your company's branded layout. Templates support individual commission line items, bonus target entries, totals, and all key payslip metadata. The template is validated on upload and an example is provided to get you started.

[SCREENSHOT: Commission page showing payslip list and the Templates tab]

### Account-Wide and Person-Specific Bonus Targets

Create bonus targets scoped to the entire team, a specific salesperson, or a specific campaign (with optional zone-level focus). Each target has a monetary goal, a bonus payout amount, a date range, and optionally a product filter. Progress is tracked in real time and contributing sales are listed in the target detail view.

---

## Dashboard & Reporting

### Dynamic Dashboard System

Build fully custom dashboards from a library of widget types: metric cards, KPI cards with target comparison, bar, line, area, pie, and doughnut charts, data tables, and link widgets. Not sure where to start? Pick from a growing collection of pre-built widget templates — one click adds a ready-made widget that you can customise from there. Dashboards can be private or shared with granular view/edit permissions per user or role. Each widget auto-refreshes every 60 seconds and can pull from any data source — sales, commissions, interactions, leads, zones, bonus targets, inventory, and more.

[SCREENSHOT: Example dashboard with KPI cards, a bar chart, and a data table side by side]

### User Profiles with KPIs

Every team member now has a profile page with their personal KPIs: sales count, commission earned, targets hit, and activity over time. Managers can review individual performance without building a custom dashboard for each rep.

### Daily Welcome Message

When sales reps open the app at the start of their day, they are greeted with a personalised welcome message showing their current KPIs — sales today, open leads, upcoming follow-ups. It is a lightweight way for managers to keep everyone aligned without sending separate briefings.

